  "text": "In terms of Y402H variant, Grassi et al. 15 reported considerable ethnic variations and also suggested that other unidentified genetic factors evidently importantly contribute to the pathogenesis of AMD. The frequency of Y402H in Asians as determined by the International HapMap Project is much lower than in Caucasians (i.e., 8.1% in Japanese and 6.8% in Chinese versus more than 35% in Caucasians). 15 In the present study, the frequency of the risk allele C was found to be 7.97%. Moreover, in agreement with our results, previous studies conducted in Japanese and Chinese populations concluded that the Y402H variant is not definitively associated with exudative AMD. 16 -19 The only SNP reported in the CFH promoter Ϫ275CϾT was found to be unrelated to AMD in Caucasians. [CITATION_1] 8 However, this association has been reported in China, 19 and we also detected a significant association in our study population. On the other hand, I62V has been reported to be associated with AMD in Caucasians, [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] Chinese, 19 and Japanese. 17 Furthermore, Caucasians 6 and Chinese 19 homozygous for the C allele of IVS15 have been reported to have a higher risk of developing AMD.",
